a\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">MOHAMED-SALIH, Veronica. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.analize-journal.ro/library/files/numarul_4/4_6_veronica_mohamed-salih.pdf\">\"Stereotypes regarding Muslim men and Muslim women on the Romanian Internet: a qualitative comparative analysis for 2004-2009 and 2010-2015\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>Journal of Gender and Feminist Studies</i> (4)<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">4 September</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Gender+and+Feminist+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=Stereotypes+regarding+Muslim+men+and+Muslim+women+on+the+Romanian+Internet%3A+a+qualitative+comparative+analysis+for+2004-2009+and+2010-2015&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.aulast=MOHAMED-SALIH&amp;rft.aufirst=Veronica&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.analize-journal.ro%2Flibrary%2Ffiles%2Fnumarul_4%2F4_6_veronica_mohamed-salih.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHijabophobia\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Hamzeh-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Hamzeh_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Hamzeh, Manal (2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=EQIoDwAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA9\"><i>Pedagogies of Deveiling: Muslim Girls and the Hijab Discourse</i></a>. IAP. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781617357244\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781617357244\